And the [D7]darkness brings a guilty conscience
[G7]When the candle's gone
Now my [C]husband back at home
And the wife he left alone
[F]Are forgotten as wine and passion [G7]whirl
But [C]who's to take the blame
For that solid wall of shame
That [F]borders on our [G7]candle lighted [C]world
